data.title: HK Pedder Street
data.meta_description: My favorite "plaque" On the pedder street side of the Landmark Building marked the location of the shore line for Victoria harbour in 1841. It is absolutely scandalous how much of the harbour has been 'reclaimed' The latest victim is the Star central ferry terminal which is being knocked down to make way for a shopping mall (as if we needed another one in HK) and a road. I expect to find the plaque for the terminal somewhere logical like under the road flyover
